        "code": {
          "language": "plaintext",
          "showLineNumbers": false,
          "showMiniMap": false
        },
        "content": "## Kubernetes Events and logs\n\nUse the dashboard variables (`namespace`, `pool`, `pod`, `model`) when narrowing an incident.\n\n```bash\n# ModelClaim status and Events\nkubectl get modelclaims -n $namespace\nkubectl describe modelclaim <claim-name> -n $namespace\nkubectl get events -n $namespace --field-selector involvedObject.kind=ModelClaim --sort-by=.lastTimestamp\n\n# Warm-pool Pods and runtime sidecar logs\nkubectl get pods -n $namespace -l pool.aibrix.ai/name=$pool\nkubectl describe pod $pod -n $namespace\nkubectl logs -n $namespace $pod -c aibrix-runtime --tail=200\n\n# Warm-pool policy validation failures (Pool Policy Valid tile). Persistent source of truth is the metric:\n#   PromQL: aibrix_modelclaim_pool_policy_valid == 0   ->  offending {namespace, deployment}\n# A one-time Warning Event is also emitted when a policy first breaks (may have since expired):\nkubectl get events -n $namespace --field-selector reason=InvalidPoolPolicy --sort-by=.lastTimestamp\n# Inspect the offending Deployment's annotation:\nkubectl get deploy DEPLOYMENT -n $namespace -o jsonpath='{.metadata.annotations.pool\\.aibrix\\.ai/policy}'\n\n# Controller-manager ModelClaim reconcile / policy logs\nkubectl logs -n aibrix-system deploy/aibrix-controller-manager --tail=200 | grep -i modelclaim\n```\n\n**Not on this dashboard yet** (tracked in [#2455](https://github.com/vllm-project/aibrix/issues/2455)): sleeping/failed phase gauges, engine restart / restart-budget, agent re-adoption, pool-policy apply/skip/fail, sleep/wake activity, no-ready duration, and HBM headroom.",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
      "pluginVersion": "11.3.1",
      "title": "Events / logs cheat sheet",
      "type": "text"
    }
